name: Cachapas from Venezuela
author: Mariposa
summary: Cachapas are traditional to Venezuela. They are a corn pancake that are so delicious and very easy to make.  Traditionally they are topped with cheese or meat. Add a little butter on top and queso blanco or any cheese you like. They are loved by all ages.
ingredients: 2 (15.25 ounce) cans whole kernel corn, drained
directions: Blend corn, milk, egg,  , sugar, and salt together in a blender until the mixture has the consistency of pancake batter
Heat oil in a a large skillet over medium heat
Add enough batter to form the size of a taco shell, 4 to 5 inches around
Cook until golden brown, about 2 minutes per side
